      • populateObject

        protected java.lang.Object populateObject(java.lang.Object o,
                                          java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> contents,
                                          java.lang.Class<?> clazz)
                                   throws ReadException
        Populates an instance of an object based on its deserialized contents. That is, this method is expected to "fill" the object's member fields with deserialized data.
        Parameters:
        o - The object to use as the basis for the population
        contents - The deserialized member fields of the object
        clazz - The class this object should be an instance of
        Returns:
        A populated instance of the object. Note that this can be a different instance than the one passed through o.
        Throws:
        ReadException - If the operation cannot be carried on
